In MATLAB, to multiply two arrays element-wise, you use the `.*` operator. However, since both arrays you mentioned contain only one element, it's a straightforward multiplication. Here's how you can do it:

```matlab
array1 = [3];
array2 = [6];
result = array1 .* array2;
```

This code will multiply the single element in `array1` by the single element in `array2`, resulting in `result` being `[18]`. If you want to multiply arrays with more elements, ensure they are of the same size for element-wise multiplication.
